        Social Proof for Wedding Photographers
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1.2rem;color:#555;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        Engaged couples spend months researching photographers before booking. Your portfolio gets them interested — your past couples' words close the deal. SocialProof makes it effortless to collect heartfelt testimonials and display them right where couples are deciding.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Why testimonials are everything in wedding photography</h2>
      <p>Wedding photography is a once-in-a-lifetime decision with no do-overs. Couples aren't just buying photos — they're trusting you to be invisible when needed and present when it counts. That trust has to be earned before you ever meet them. Testimonials from past brides and grooms are the most powerful shortcut to that trust.</p>
      <p style="margin-top:1rem;">A portfolio shows style. Testimonials show character. Couples want to know: Are you easy to work with? Did you nail the candid shots? Did the photos arrive on time? Did you make them feel comfortable? No portfolio answers those questions — but past couples can.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">What couples actually want to read</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li><strong>Personality & ease:</strong> "We forgot the camera was there — she made us feel so natural."</li>
        <li><strong>Delivery:</strong> "Our gallery was ready in three weeks. We cried opening it."</li>
        <li><strong>Crisis handling:</strong> "Rain on our wedding day — she adapted without missing a single moment."</li>
        <li><strong>Communication:</strong> "Responded to every email within hours. No anxiety ever."</li>
        <li><strong>Value:</strong> "Worth every penny. These photos will outlast everything else from that day."</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">How SocialProof works for your photography business</h2>
      <ol style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
